  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The forthcoming book \"Art, Identity and Cosmopolitanism,\" to be published by Peter Lang Verlag in 2024, aims to contribute to discussions on the intersections of art, identity, and global citizenship. Through its exploration of these themes, it serves as a pedagogical anchor, supported by library holdings in 3 institutions, highlighting its potential for educational impact and relevance to sustainability policy.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Art, Identity and Cosmopolitanism\" is set to be released by Peter Lang Verlag in 2024. This scholarly work contextualizes art within a framework of identity and global citizenship, striving to explore how artistic expressions shape and reflect collective identities in an increasingly interconnected world. Its thematic focus positions it not only within the confines of art history but also at the crossroads of philosophy, sociology, and cultural studies.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book is evaluated as a significant pedagogical anchor, indicated by its library holdings in at least three institutions. This suggests a degree of academic interest and support that can foster its use in educational settings. The potential for this text to be utilized in courses underscores its relevance to contemporary discussions in both arts and humanities disciplines.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Additionally, the work possesses sustainability and policy relevance, as inferred from its connection to one Sustainable Development Goal (SDG). This emphasis on sustainability provides a valuable perspective that aligns art with broader social and ecological concerns, making it a critical resource for scholars and practitioners interested in these vital issues.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While there are currently no active citations or online mentions, the foundational concepts presented in \"Art, Identity and Cosmopolitanism\" have the potential to resonate across multiple fields of inquiry. As the book becomes available, its scholarly and social implications may unfold, leading to greater discourse and exploration of its themes in both academic circles and broader societal contexts.</p>",
